# Cloudflare Pages static-header rules.
#
# We previously set Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin +
# Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: credentialless to enable SharedArrayBuffer
# for FFmpeg.wasm inside the legacy in-browser Create Video modal.
# Those headers turned out to break Firebase Auth — the auth iframe at
# https://<project>.firebaseapp.com/__/auth/iframe doesn't ship COEP
# headers, so the embedder policy blocked it with NS_ERROR_DOM_COEP_FAILED,
# which killed BOTH signInWithPopup and signInWithRedirect.
#
# In-browser video encoding is no longer the primary path — the AI Video
# panel renders server-side via Wan 2.2 S2V — so we trade FFmpeg.wasm for
# working sign-in. Leave this file empty (Cloudflare Pages still serves it,
# just with no header overrides) so the auth iframe loads cleanly.
